<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alliliel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Im trying to make a social that has a few lines in one /guildsay.<P>/gui Thank you %T for your donation to the Clerics of Tunare fund for the Relief of Poor Alliliels!<P>It won't let me type that much in one line, and if I split it up in 2 lines like this...<P>/gui Thank you %T for your donation to the Clerics of <BR>/gui Tunare fund for the Relief of Poor Alliliels!<P>it doesn't use the second line.<P>Is there a trick to this I'm missing?<P>------------------<BR><B>Alliliel Archfalcon</B><BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR><A HREF="http://www.kriegeronline.com" TARGET=_blank>Krieger</A><BR>Tunare Server is my uber-guild</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Unfortunately I don't know of a way to do that.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif">  Have the same problem with /auc.<P>/sigh</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Catroina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I had the same problem making multi line shouts. Basically only the first line would be displayed to everyone else. What I found if I put a small pause between the lines then it worked ok. For example the social would be: <BR>Line 1: /Shout   Somthing you want to say<BR>line 2: Pause 10 <BR>Line 3: /Shout Something else you want to say<P>I haven't tried it out with guildsay but perhaps something like that would work for you.<P>------------------<BR>Cleric of the 42 Season<BR>Emarr.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah. There's apparently a server side thing that doesn't let you submit more than one line of text every half a sec or so. Probably so you can't spam people anymore. It used to work (ever taught someone another language with a spam hotkey?).<P>I find /pause 5 is sufficient to keep it spaced without spamming<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Templar of Prexus<BR>Cohort Chalybeius<BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Always had that problem with /auc. If it's now the same with /g, that's new to me.<P>I have a hotkey that says:<P>/cast 3<BR>/g Casting complete heal on %T because %O is<BR>/assist<BR>/g getting owned by %T!<P><BR>(erm I think it's %O... whichever one is the pronoun)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually, now that you mention it it probably doesn't affect /g because /g only affects a max of 6 people where as /shout, /auc, /gu and /ooc are considered spam (ie you can turn off seeing them but not getting the messages)<P>I'll try it next time I log on.<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Templar of Prexus<BR>Cohort Chalybeius<BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Samsara</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm....I've been doing some auctioning in FV with one of my characters the past few days.  And she started out with five /auc lines of stuff.  I didn't have any problem seeing them go out on my end but now I wonder whether other people saw them.  Come to think of it, it's only been the stuff in the first line that has sold *chuckle*.<P>Wow, would I feel dumb.  So how do you know it's not getting sent?  Do you not see it on your screen or are people just telling you that your message seems cut off?<P><P>------------------<BR>Samsara<BR>Holy Cleric of Tunare<BR>The Folk of Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gniss Fleshmender</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/g hotkeys with 5 lines now get sent slower than they used to. I used to be able to spam language so hard I'd LD myself, now I'm only able to send the next set when the first set finishes.<P>------------------<BR>The patchwork cleric<BR>Domus Divinae<BR>Prexus</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ajax34i</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you have 5 lines of auc you see 5 lines being sent but they only see the first line.  Pretty sure that's how it works.  You have to put the pauses in there for it to work.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I never could get the pause to make the /auc thing work. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I did.<P>/auc xxx,xxx,xxx<BR>/pause 5<BR>/auc xxx,xxx,xxx<BR>/pause 5<BR>/auc xxx,xxx,xxx<P>sends 3 auctions spaced 2.5 seconds apart and it works fine for me. If it doesn;t work for you, use /pause 10.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sphynkl</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ack, I didn't know that multiple lines didn't work..or only first line, weren't shown up on ooc/auc/shout.<P>No wonder I can't sell this crap I'm toting around.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
